com.camerontec.util.logger.hpl

Class HighPerformanceLogger

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.logger.hpl.HighPerformanceLogger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ILogger, org.slf4j.Logger

    public final class HighPerformanceLogger
extends Object
implements ILogger
    High performance logger implementation.

    This implementation performs the basic tasks of:

    • Filtering out logs that are not enabled
    • Populating pre-allocated thread local logging events and delegating them to the specified IHighPerformanceLoggerAppender (which it assumes is thread safe)
    • Providing special first order support for logging of BytesSegments to avoid java.lang.String creation.

    This implementation does not currently support the org.slf4j.Marker methods.
